A small distillery with a big heart and a keen passion for the environment has been making waves on the Isle of Islay, on the ‘whisky coast’ of west Scotland. This was done by reconnecting the land and the dram, re-evaluating the prescribed ‘rules’ of the industry, questioning where flavour comes from and understanding why agricultural ecosystems are important. The natural evolution of this outlook is ‘We Also Make Whisky’, an international campaign designed to showcase the difference that can be made when looking beyond profit, to a more holistic approach.
